      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SARAQAEL (1) won and then placed here at this level, before tackling a $100,000 QTIS 3&4yo Classic at the track, where he folded up from the speed well-supported. This suits a lot better, and Satherley rides and trains. He's won 5/13 and 4x at the track and can add to that record. WAYNO (6) didn't manage the 13 gate here last time, but his form prior stacks right up. Tackles this distance for the first time, and it's likely to suit. BETTERLUCKNEXTTIME (2) was outgraded at Eagle Farm last time but went close over 1300m in a 70 at Toowoomba prior. Was narrowly beaten in a 68 at Doomben in January and can use the inside gate. Well placed, so expecting a strong run. LEICA FLAMINGO (4) is free running and followed a comfortable Maiden win this track/trip with a near miss at Mackay. This is tougher, but she sits down in the weights and will give a sight.",
